{"word":"γεραιός","slug":"γεραιός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γεραιός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:γηραιός'><el>γηραιός</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γέρων'><el>γέρων</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>old</i>, in <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b> and <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; of men, with notion of dignity, like <i>signor</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; <el>ὁ γεραιός</el> <i>that reverend sire</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>γεραίτερος</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <el>οἱ γεραίτεροι</el> <i>the elders, senators</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>γέρων</el>:— <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>γεραίτατος</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; rarely = <el>πρεσβύτατος</el>, <i>eldest</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of things, <i>ancient</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}